headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 23 points, Cole Anthony came off the bench with 18 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Boston Celtics 96-76 on Wednesday night to clinch seventh place in the Eastern Conference and the top spot in the play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic clinch 7th spot in Eastern Conference with 96-76 win over depleted Celtics

headlines.description: — Jeff Dowtin Jr. scored a career-high 30 points and the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a 12-game losing streak with a 122-103 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dowtin scores a career-high 30 points and 76ers snap 12-game skid with 122-103 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Jonathan Mogbo had 17 points, a career-high 11 assists and 10 rebounds for the first triple-double by a rookie in the NBA this season, helping the Toronto Raptors beat the short-handed Charlotte Hornets 126-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mogbo becomes 1st NBA rookie with a triple-double this season, helps Raptors beat Hornets

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 45 points in his first game in Dallas since being traded to the Los Angeles, helping the Lakers wrap up a playoff spot with a 112-97 victory over the Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 45 points in Dallas return as Lakers clinch playoff spot with 112-97 win

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey dominated with 28 points, 16 rebounds and 11 assists and the Chicago Bulls beat the Miami Heat 119-111 Wednesday night in a game with heavy seeding implications.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey dominates with 28 points, 16 rebounds and 11 assists as Bulls beat Heat 119-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Kyle Filipowski scored 30 points including a dunk that sent the game into overtime and grabbed 18 rebounds as the Utah Jazz snapped a nine-game losing streak with a 133-126 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Filipowski scores 30 and the Jazz win 133-126 in OT against the Trail Blazers

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes made a 3-pointer at the buzzer after committing a foul moments earlier that could have cost his team, and the San Antonio Spurs stunned the Golden State Warriors 114-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harrison Barnes swishes 3-pointer at the buzzer as Spurs stun Warriors with 114-111 win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 33 points, Chet Holmgren added 22 and the short-handed Oklahoma City Thunder beat Phoenix 125-112 on Wednesday night, eliminating the Suns from the playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Williams scores 33 to lead Thunder past Suns, who were eliminated from playoff race

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had his 32nd triple-double of the season with 20 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists and Denver beat the Sacramento Kings 124-116 on Wednesday night in the Nuggets' first game since head <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 32nd triple-double to lead Nuggets past Kings 124-116 in Denver's 1st game without Malone

headlines.description: — James Harden had 35 points and 10 assists and the streaking Los Angeles Clippers beat the playoff-bound Houston Rockets 134-117 on Wednesday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers extend winning streak to 6 games with 134-117 win over short-handed Rockets
